Enzyme Assay: In order to test the selectivity of substituents on piperazinotriazole ring within the PARP family, the selectivity of compound S3 and positive compound AZD2281 were tested.
Enzyme Assay: In order to test the selectivity of substituents on piperazinotriazole ring within the PARP family, the selectivity of compound S3 and positive compound AZD2281 were tested.

PARP-2 and PARP-3 Enzymatic Assay: PARP-2 and PARP-3 enzymatic assays were conducted using commercial PARP-2/PARP-3 Chemiluminescent Assay Kit (BPS Biosciences) and the protocols with the kits. Briefly, histones were coated in a high binding plate first, and incubated with PARP-2 or PARP-3, and increasing concentrations of compounds for 0.5 h. Then, biotinylated NAD and activated DNA were added to the wells. The biotinylated PARylation product was measured by adding streptavidin-HRP and HRP substrates which produce chemiluminescence.
